# Import Style

- Follow the Python import order conventions
    - Built-in modules (os, sys, json)
    - Third-party packages (requests, numpy, pandas)
    - Local application imports (from tools.package import module)
    - Separate each group with a blank line
    - Sort imports alphabetically within each group
    - Use import module before from module import item
    - Avoid wildcard imports (from module import *)
- Prefer absolute imports over relative imports.
- Example: Use `from src.tasks.summarize_task import GenerateSummaryTask` instead of `from .summarize_task import GenerateSummaryTask`.
- This makes the code more explicit and easier to understand and maintain, especially in larger projects.
